Step 1 — Update the resource type in main.tf

Find every occurrence of aws_s3_bucket_object and replace with aws_s3_object:
# BEFORE
resource "aws_s3_bucket_object" "my_object" {
  bucket       = aws_s3_bucket.my_bucket.id
  key          = "app/config.json"
  content      = "Hello World"
  content_type = "text/plain"
}

# AFTER
resource "aws_s3_object" "my_object" {
  bucket       = aws_s3_bucket.my_bucket.id
  key          = "app/config.json"
  content      = "Hello World"
  content_type = "text/plain"
}
💡 Replace in every place it appears in the given file — there may be multiple occurrences

Step 2 — Update provider version in versions.tf
# BEFORE
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 3.0"     # ← old
    }
  }
}

# AFTER
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"     # ← updated
    }
  }
}

Step 3 — Run terraform init -upgrade
terraform init -upgrade
Expected output:
- Installing hashicorp/aws v5.x.x...
- Installed hashicorp/aws v5.x.x

Terraform has been successfully initialized!

Step 4 — Run terraform validate
terraform validate
Expected output:
Success! The configuration is valid.

